commit message: Fix .gitignore and prefgen settings after rename

Support for testing non-null values

This is for the case where we want to ensure a value is present but don't
particularly care what its actual value is.

Add a tool to munge test files.

caltool.py converts test files into .ics files for importing. It allows test
cases to remain minimal by excluding irrelevant items. Valid .ics files are
generated by supplying missing properties.

Test files can also be converted into 'real' calendars to test round-tripping
of the various test cases via other s/w.

Fix organizer handling, add test.

This fixes the parsing and output of organizer so that it contains just the
actual to: part of the mailto: URI. This should fix the value in the Android
DB and so fix any check where the calendar owner is compared to the
organizer. It doesn't tell us why GUESTS_CAN_MODIFY isn't working however.
Lets see if this is enough to fix #29 for the reporting user.
Update the version code for the #29 organizer fix

Scroll the view down when Load is clicked

Issue #27 was not an app error but user confusion due to the Insert/Delete
buttons being hidden on their screen. Scroll the view to make the buttons
visible when shown in order to prevent confusion in the future.
Update version to 2.1 for new release
